---
export const prerender = true;
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="About" description="Learn about this Astro Feature Showcase project and how it demonstrates Astro's rendering modes on Contentstack Launch.">
  <div class="container" style="max-width: 800px; padding: 4rem 1.5rem;">
    <div class="page-header" style="text-align: left; padding: 2rem 0 3rem;">
      <div class="badge badge-ssg mb-2">⚡ SSG Page</div>
      <h1 style="color: #fff; margin: 1rem 0;">About This Project</h1>
      <p style="color: var(--color-text-muted); font-size: 1.1rem; max-width: 60ch;">
        A hands-on showcase of every major Astro v5 feature, built specifically for deployment on Contentstack Launch.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose">
      <h2>What is this?</h2>
      <p>
        This project is a <strong>comprehensive Astro application</strong> designed to demonstrate and test every major feature
        of the Astro web framework in a real production environment on Contentstack Launch.
      </p>

      <h2>Features Covered</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Static Site Generation (SSG)</strong> — Build-time rendering for maximum performance</li>
        <li><strong>Server-Side Rendering (SSR)</strong> — Per-request rendering for dynamic, personalized content</li>
        <li><strong>Hybrid Mode</strong> — Mix SSG and SSR in the same project using <code>output: "hybrid"</code></li>
        <li><strong>Islands Architecture</strong> — Isolated React components with partial hydration directives</li>
        <li><strong>Content Collections</strong> — Type-safe Markdown/MDX content with Zod schema validation</li>
        <li><strong>API Routes</strong> — File-based REST endpoints (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE)</li>
        <li><strong>Middleware</strong> — Per-request interceptors for logging, auth, and injecting locals</li>
        <li><strong>View Transitions</strong> — Native browser page transition animations</li>
        <li><strong>Image Optimization</strong> — Built-in <code>&lt;Image&gt;</code> component with lazy loading</li>
        <li><strong>Sitemap Generation</strong> — Auto-generated <code>sitemap-index.xml</code> via <code>@astrojs/sitemap</code></li>
        <li><strong>MDX</strong> — Embed React components inside Markdown content</li>
        <li><strong>TypeScript</strong> — End-to-end type safety with strict config</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Tech Stack</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Framework:</strong> <a href="https://astro.build" target="_blank">Astro v5</a></li>
        <li><strong>Adapter:</strong> <code>@astrojs/node</code> (standalone mode)</li>
        <li><strong>UI Framework:</strong> React 19 (for Islands)</li>
        <li><strong>Content:</strong> Markdown + MDX via <code>@astrojs/mdx</code></li>
        <li><strong>Hosting:</strong> <a href="https://www.contentstack.com/products/launch" target="_blank">Contentstack Launch</a></li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Rendering Strategy</h2>
      <p>
        The project uses <code>output: "hybrid"</code> which makes all pages SSG by default.
        Pages that need server-side data add <code>export const prerender = false</code> to opt into SSR.
        API routes are always SSR.
      </p>

      <h2>Deployment</h2>
      <p>
        This app is deployed on <strong>Contentstack Launch</strong>, a Git-connected hosting platform.
        The <code>@astrojs/node</code> adapter in standalone mode produces a self-contained Node.js server at
        <code>dist/server/entry.mjs</code> which Launch runs via the <code>npm start</code> command.
      </p>

      <h2>Project Structure</h2>
      <pre>
src/
├── components/     # Reusable Astro + React components
├── content/
│   ├── config.ts   # Zod collection schemas
│   └── blog/       # Markdown & MDX posts
├── layouts/        # Page layouts with ViewTransitions
├── middleware/     # Astro middleware (logging, locals)
├── pages/
│   ├── api/        # API routes (SSR endpoints)
│   ├── blog/       # Blog pages (SSG)
│   ├── ssr/        # SSR demo pages
│   └── ...         # Other pages
└── styles/         # Global CSS
      </pre>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
